          <heading>Incompetency of recipient</heading>
          <content>
            <p>§346-38  Incompetency of recipient.
If
the recipient is found incapable of taking care of the recipient's money or
oneself, the department of human services may direct its assistance to be paid
to a legal guardian or any other reputable person for the recipient's benefit
or may suspend assistance for such period as it deems fit. [L 1941, c 296, pt
of §1; RL 1945, §4844; RL 1955, §108-24; HRS §346-38; am L 1970, c 105, §5; gen
ch 1985; am L 1987, c 339, §4]
